   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Section 2: Pairwise Particle Relationships\n",
    "\n",
    "The central idea of the Particle Transformer: in addition to per-particle features, the model receives information about **relationships between pairs** of particles.\n",
    "\n",
    "Knowing that particle A has $p_T = 50$ GeV and particle B has $p_T = 45$ GeV is useful. Knowing additionally that they are separated by $\\Delta R = 0.1$ with a combined invariant mass near 80 GeV makes it much more likely they came from a W boson decay.\n",
    "\n",
    "ParT uses four pairwise features, each capturing a different aspect of the two-particle relationship."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2a. Angular Distance: $\\Delta R_{ij} = \\sqrt{\\Delta\\eta^2 + \\Delta\\phi^2}$\n",
    "\n",
    "$\\Delta R$ measures the angular separation between two particles in the $\\eta$-$\\phi$ plane.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2b. $k_{T,ij} = \\min(p_{T,i},\\, p_{T,j}) \\times \\Delta R_{ij}$\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "This quantity is closely related to the jet clustering distance in algorithms like anti-$k_T$. It encodes information about the splitting history of the jet."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2c.  $z_{ij} = \\frac{\\min(p_{T,i},\\, p_{T,j})}{p_{T,i} + p_{T,j}}$\n",
    "\n",
    "$z$ measures the momentum balance between two particles.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2d. Invariant Mass: $m^2_{ij} = (p_i + p_j)^2$\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Exercise 1: Compute pairwise $\\Delta R$\n",
    "\n",
    "Compute $\\Delta R_{ij}$ for all particle pairs in a jet. Fill in the formula.\n",
    "\n",
    "Reminder: $\\Delta R_{ij} = \\sqrt{(\\eta_i - \\eta_j)^2 + (\\phi_i - \\phi_j)^2}$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def compute_pairwise_deltaR(eta, phi):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Compute the Delta R matrix for all particle pairs.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Args:\n",
    "        eta: array of shape (n_particles,) -- pseudorapidity of each particle\n",
    "        phi: array of shape (n_particles,) -- azimuthal angle of each particle\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "        deltaR: array of shape (n_particles, n_particles)\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    # Compute differences using broadcasting:\n",
    "    # eta[:, None] has shape (n, 1), eta[None, :] has shape (1, n)\n",
    "    # Subtracting gives shape (n, n)\n",
    "    deta = eta[:, None] - eta[None, :]\n",
    "    dphi = phi[:, None] - phi[None, :]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Wrap dphi to [-pi, pi] (angles are periodic!)\n",
    "    dphi = np.mod(dphi + np.pi, 2 * np.pi) - np.pi\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # === YOUR CODE HERE (1 line) ===\n",
    "    # Compute deltaR from deta and dphi\n",
    "    deltaR = ...  # FILL IN: sqrt(deta^2 + dphi^2)\n",
    "    # ===============================\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return deltaR"
   ]
  },
