    "### Architecture Observations\n",
    "\n",
    "- **The pair embedding is small**: 4 input features $\\to$ 8 output values (one per head). This small network is what encodes the physics prior into attention.\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Most parameters are in the transformer blocks**, dominated by attention projections and feed-forward networks -- same as standard transformers.\n",
    "\n",
    "- **ParT_full vs ParT_kin**: the only structural difference is the input embedding dimension (17 vs 7 features). The full model additionally receives particle identification variables (charge, hadron/photon/lepton flags, impact parameters). The kinematic-only model is already strong on its own.\n",
    "\n",
    "- **The CLS token**: 128 learnable parameters. It is the sole aggregation point for jet-level classification."
