   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Section 6: What Does ParT Learn? Interpretability\n",
    "\n",
    "Transformer attention weights are directly inspectable, and the patterns that emerge reveal what the model has learned about jet physics.\n",
    "\n",
    "Wang et al. (2024) conducted a detailed interpretability study of the Particle Transformer in *\"Interpreting Transformers for Jet Tagging\"* ([arXiv:2412.03673](https://arxiv.org/abs/2412.03673)). The key findings are summarized below."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Finding 1: Sparse, Binary Attention\n",
    "\n",
    "The softmax can produce any probability distribution, but the trained model converges to nearly binary attention weights. Each particle attends strongly to at most one other particle, with all other weights close to zero. This sparsity is not imposed by the architecture -- the model learns it on its own.\n",
    "\n",
    "The result is that attention effectively pairs up particles, forming a tree-like structure.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Finding 2: Substructure Discovery\n",
    "\n",
    "The attention patterns align with physical substructure:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **H $\\to$ bb jets**: attention links particles within the same b-quark subjet, identifying the two-prong structure.\n",
    "- **Top quark jets** (t $\\to$ bW $\\to$ bqq): attention identifies the three-prong structure.\n",
    "- **QCD jets**: attention follows patterns consistent with the parton shower splitting tree.\n",
    "\n",
    "The model discovers jet substructure -- subjets, decay chains, splitting trees -- purely from the classification objective, without explicit supervision on these features.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Finding 3: Head Specialization\n",
    "\n",
    "Different attention heads specialize in different aspects of jet physics:\n",
    "- Some heads focus on angular proximity (small $\\Delta R$ pairs)\n",
    "- Others weight momentum-based relationships (high $k_T$ or specific $z$ ranges)\n",
    "- Some heads capture global jet structure while others attend to local neighborhoods\n",
    "\n",
    "This is analogous to how CNN filters specialize in different visual features, but here the specialization is over physics-based particle relationships."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Visualizing the Interpretability Findings\n",
    "\n",
    "We run the pre-trained `ParT_full` model and read its attention weights directly. The model is defined in [`part_model.py`](part_model.py) (adapted from [aaronw5/Interpreting-Particle-Transformers](https://github.com/aaronw5/Interpreting-Particle-Transformers), with the `weaver` dependency removed so it runs on a plain PyTorch install). Each transformer block stores the attention matrix from its forward pass; [`part_utils.py`](part_utils.py) builds the 17 input features and runs the model.\n",
    "\n",
    "We pass three multi-prong jets -- H $\\to$ 4q, top $\\to$ bqq, and top $\\to$ b$\\ell\\nu$ -- through the model in a single forward pass and plot the attention from one head per jet."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Run the pre-trained ParT_full model and read out its attention weights\n",
    "from matplotlib.collections import LineCollection\n",
    "from part_utils import load_part_full, build_part_inputs, run_attention, LABELS\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load eta/phi (relative to the jet axis) and pT for the jet displays\n",
    "x_disp, _, y_disp = read_file(data_file, particle_features=['part_deta', 'part_dphi', 'part_pt'])\n",
    "disp_labels = y_disp.argmax(1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Three multi-prong jets: H->4q (4-prong), top->bqq (3-prong), top->blv (semileptonic)\n",
    "picks = [('H->4q', 4), ('top->bqq', 8), ('top->blv', 9)]\n",
    "indices = [int(np.where(disp_labels == c)[0][0]) for _, c in picks]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load weights and run a single forward pass on the 3 jets\n",
    "model = load_part_full('models/ParT_full.pt')\n",
    "feats, vecs, mask = build_part_inputs(data_file, indices)\n",
    "probs, attn = run_attention(model, feats, vecs, mask)   # attn: list of 8 layers, (3, 8, P, P)\n",
    "print(\"Predictions:\")\n",
    "for (name, _), p in zip(picks, probs):\n",
    "    print(f\"  {name:9s} -> {LABELS[int(p.argmax())]}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "LAYER = 5  # 0-indexed transformer block to visualize\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 3, figsize=(16, 10))\n",
    "for col, ((name, _), jet_idx) in enumerate(zip(picks, indices)):\n",
    "    deta, dphi, pt = x_disp[jet_idx, 0], x_disp[jet_idx, 1], x_disp[jet_idx, 2]\n",
    "    nr = int(mask[col, 0].sum())  # number of real (non-padded) particles\n",
    "\n",
    "    # In this layer, pick the head with the most concentrated (\"binary\") attention\n",
    "    head_top1 = [np.sort(attn[LAYER][col, h, :nr, :nr].numpy(), 1)[:, -1].mean() for h in range(8)]\n",
    "    head = int(np.argmax(head_top1))\n",
    "    A = attn[LAYER][col, head, :nr, :nr].numpy()\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Top row: eta-phi display, particles sized by pT, red edges = strongest attention link\n",
    "    ax = axes[0, col]\n",
    "    ax.scatter(deta[:nr], dphi[:nr], s=20 + 400 * pt[:nr] / (pt[:nr].max() + 1e-9),\n",
    "               c='#3498db', edgecolors='k', linewidths=0.5, alpha=0.9, zorder=3)\n",
    "    segs = [[(deta[i], dphi[i]), (deta[int(A[i].argmax())], dphi[int(A[i].argmax())])] for i in range(nr)]\n",
    "    lws = [0.3 + 3.0 * A[i, int(A[i].argmax())] for i in range(nr)]\n",
    "    ax.add_collection(LineCollection(segs, colors='#e74c3c', linewidths=lws, alpha=0.5, zorder=2))\n",
    "    ax.set_title(f'{name} jet\\nattention edges -- layer {LAYER+1}, head {head+1}')\n",
    "    ax.set_xlabel(r'$\\Delta\\eta$'); ax.set_ylabel(r'$\\Delta\\phi$')\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Bottom row: the attention matrix for that head\n",
    "    ax = axes[1, col]\n",
    "    im = ax.imshow(A, origin='lower', cmap='viridis', aspect='equal')\n",
    "    fig.colorbar(im, ax=ax, fraction=0.046)\n",
    "    ax.set_title(f'Attention matrix (layer {LAYER+1}, head {head+1})\\n'\n",
    "                 f'mean top-1 weight = {head_top1[head]:.2f}')\n",
    "    ax.set_xlabel('Key particle $j$'); ax.set_ylabel('Query particle $i$')\n",
    "\n",
    "fig.suptitle('Attention from the pre-trained Particle Transformer (ParT_full)', fontsize=15, y=1.0)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
